Foot and mouth disease, China (People's Rep. of)
------------------------------------------------
Information received on 24 May 2013 from Dr Zhang Zhongqui, Director General, China Animal Disease Control Centre, Veterinary Bureau, Ministry of Agriculture, Beijing, China (People's Rep. of)

Summary
Report type: Follow-up report No. 3
Date of start of the event: 12 Apr 2013
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 22 Apr 2013
Report date: 24 May 2013
Date submitted to OIE: 24 May 2013
Reason for notification: New strain of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Foot and mouth disease virus
Serotype: A
Nature of diagnosis: Suspicion, Clinical, Laboratory (basic), Laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country
Related reports: Immediate notification (22 Apr 2013)
Follow-up report No. 1 (03 May 2013)
Follow-up report No. 2 (10 May 2013)
Follow-up report No. 3 (24 May 2013)

New outbreaks (1)
Outbreak 1: Yongjiu village, Bayi, Linzhi, Tibet
Date of start of the outbreak: 24 May 2013
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Village
